    <p>Ad­min­is­ter­ing a Covid-19 vac­cine to the masses will be dif­fi­cult be­cause:</p>
    <p>1</p>
    <p>There is a short time frame within which a huge num­ber of peo­ple must be in­oc­u­lated. The ob­jec­tive is to of­fer vac­cines to the most vul­ner­a­ble be­fore the end of next month, to health­care work­ers be­fore the end of Jan­uary, and to all Amer­i­cans by the be­gin­ning of April.</p>
    <p>2 3</p>
    <p>Most vac­cines will re­quire two doses.</p>
    <p>Some of the vac­cines must be stored at very low tem­per­a­tures. For in­stance, the Pfizer-BioNTech vac­cine must be stored at mi­nus 70 deg C.</p>


